 to generate the Invoker at all. This seems like a tricky situation—perhaps I need to explore the implications of the return value further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class implementation**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out if a public class that's not final can have a custom method in the helper of the same package. It seems like I might have to dive into the specific implementation details. I want to ensure I’m interpreting the rules of visibility and inheritance correctly here. It's essential to grasp how these methods interact and what constraints exist. I’ll keep poking around to get clarity!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying compilation issues**\\n\\nI'm troubleshooting the situation where I want to access `SourceCompiler$1` but can't copy it. It looks like I need to get the loader from a class compiled by `NullBytecodeCompiler`, which, unfortunately, returns null and can't compile a class. Maybe I can make it return bytecode for one class initially and null later? My flow involves creating an anchor class with the same anonymous loader to invoke it directly. This is getting a bit complicated!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing compilation flow**\\n\\nI’m figuring out why `sources.get(\\\"java.lang.String\\\")` returns null when checking the compiled map. It seems like I need to provide a source for `java.lang.String`. So, I’ll use `compiler.setSource(\\\"java.lang.String\\\", \\\"Object value(){return null;}\\\")`, turn off the system compiler, and then it looks like my `findSystemClass(\\\"java.lang.String\\\")` will succeed. However, setting the source for `java.lang.String` might compile but not be used directly. I need to ensure I'm actively working with `SourceCompiler$1` line. I'm noticing there might be a complex flow with MethodHandles at play here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OSYgSnKJBp4SnjoSO889uPXE|fc_047c067aec619fa60169f1180a2ff8819eb52ad2a39da7b575", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java/h2/SourceCompilerAnonymous1Test.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.h2.util.SourceCompiler;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.fail;\n\npublic class SourceCompilerAnonymous1Test {\n    private static final String INVOKER_CLASS_NAME = \"org.h2.util.SourceCompilerSystemFallbackInvoker\";\n    private static final String INVOKER_SOURCE = \"\"\"\n            package org.h2.util;\n\n            import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\n            import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\n            import java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\n\n            public class SourceCompilerSystemFallbackInvoker {\n                public static Class<?> exerciseFindSystemClassFallback() throws Throwable {\n                    ControlledCompiler compiler = new ControlledCompiler();\n                    compiler.setJavaSystemCompiler(false);\n                    compiler.setSource(\"h2.generated.SourceCompilerLoaderAnchor\", \"Object marker() { return null; }\");\n                    Class<?> anchorClass = compiler.getClass(\"h2.generated.SourceCompilerLoaderAnchor\");\n                    ClassLoader sourceCompilerLoader = anchorClass.getClassLoader();\n\n                    compiler.setSource(\"java.lang.String\", \"Object value() { return null; }\");\n                    compiler.returnNullBytecode = true;\n\n                    MethodHandle findClass = MethodHandles.lookup().findVirtual(\n                            sourceCompilerLoader.getClass(),\n                            \"findClass\",\n                            MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n                    return (Class<?>) findClass.invoke(sourceCompilerLoader, \"java.lang.String\");\n                }\n\n                static final class ControlledCompiler extends SourceCompiler {\n                    private boolean returnNullBytecode;\n\n                    @Override\n                    byte[] javacCompile(String packageName, String className, String source) {\n                        if (returnNullBytecode) {\n                            return null;\n                        }\n                        return super.javacCompile(packageName, className, source);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            \"\"\";\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToSystemClassLookupWhenLegacyCompilerProducesNoBytecode() throws Exception {\n        SourceCompiler compiler = new SourceCompiler();\n        compiler.setSource(INVOKER_CLASS_NAME, INVOKER_SOURCE);\n\n        assertRuntimeCompilationOutcome(() -> {\n            Method method = compiler.getMethod(INVOKER_CLASS_NAME);\n\n            assertThat(method).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(method.getName()).isEqualTo(\"exerciseFindSystemClassFallback\");\n            assertThat(method.invoke(null)).isEqualTo(String.class);\n        });\n    }\n\n    private static void assertRuntimeCompilationOutcome(CompilationAction action) throws Exception {\n        try {\n            action.run();\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException ex) {\n            assertThat(ex).hasMessageContaining(\"Defining new classes at runtime is not supported\");\n        } catch (RuntimeException ex) {\n            if (!hasUnsupportedRuntimeClassDefinitionCause(ex)) {\n                fail(\"Runtime source compilation failed before class definition\", ex);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static boolean hasUnsupportedRuntimeClassDefinitionCause(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof UnsupportedOperationException\n                    && current.getMessage() != null\n                    && current.getMessage().contains(\"Defining new classes at runtime is not supported\")) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private interface CompilationAction {\n        void run() throws Exception;\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 366, "output": 5010, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34560, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777407951271, "responseId": "resp_047c067aec619fa60169f117cfcd48819eb0428c2b8ea07849"}}
[tool-exec] start id=call_OSYgSnKJBp4SnjoSO889uPXE|fc_047c067aec619fa60169f1180a2ff8819eb52ad2a39da7b575 name=write args={"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java/h2/SourceCompilerAnonymous1Test.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.h2.util.SourceCompiler;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.fail;\n\npublic class SourceCompilerAnonymous1Test {\n    private static final String INVOKER_CLASS_NAME = \"org.h2.util.SourceCompilerSystemFallbackInvoker\";\n    private static final String INVOKER_SOURCE = \"\"\"\n            package org.h2.util;\n\n            import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\n            import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\n            import java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\n\n            public class SourceCompilerSystemFallbackInvoker {\n                public static Class<?> exerciseFindSystemClassFallback() throws Throwable {\n                    ControlledCompiler compiler = new ControlledCompiler();\n                    compiler.setJavaSystemCompiler(false);\n                    compiler.setSource(\"h2.generated.SourceCompilerLoaderAnchor\", \"Object marker() { return null; }\");\n                    Class<?> anchorClass = compiler.getClass(\"h2.generated.SourceCompilerLoaderAnchor\");\n                    ClassLoader sourceCompilerLoader = anchorClass.getClassLoader();\n\n                    compiler.setSource(\"java.lang.String\", \"Object value() { return null; }\");\n                    compiler.returnNullBytecode = true;\n\n                    MethodHandle findClass = MethodHandles.lookup().findVirtual(\n                            sourceCompilerLoader.getClass(),\n                            \"findClass\",\n                            MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n                    return (Class<?>) findClass.invoke(sourceCompilerLoader, \"java.lang.String\");\n                }\n\n                static final class ControlledCompiler extends SourceCompiler {\n                    private boolean returnNullBytecode;\n\n                    @Override\n                    byte[] javacCompile(String packageName, String className, String source) {\n                        if (returnNullBytecode) {\n                            return null;\n                        }\n                        return super.javacCompile(packageName, className, source);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            \"\"\";\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToSystemClassLookupWhenLegacyCompilerProducesNoBytecode() throws Exception {\n        SourceCompiler compiler = new SourceCompiler();\n        compiler.setSource(INVOKER_CLASS_NAME, INVOKER_SOURCE);\n\n        assertRuntimeCompilationOutcome(() -> {\n            Method method = compiler.getMethod(INVOKER_CLASS_NAME);\n\n            assertThat(method).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(method.getName()).isEqualTo(\"exerciseFindSystemClassFallback\");\n            assertThat(method.invoke(null)).isEqualTo(String.class);\n        });\n    }\n\n    private static void assertRuntimeCompilationOutcome(CompilationAction action) throws Exception {\n        try {\n            action.run();\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException ex) {\n            assertThat(ex).hasMessageContaining(\"Defining new classes at runtime is not supported\");\n        } catch (RuntimeException ex) {\n            if (!hasUnsupportedRuntimeClassDefinitionCause(ex)) {\n                fail(\"Runtime source compilation failed before class definition\", ex);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static boolean hasUnsupportedRuntimeClassDefinitionCause(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof UnsupportedOperationException\n                    && current.getMessage() != null\n                    && current.getMessage().contains(\"Defining new classes at runtime is not supported\")) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private interface CompilationAction {\n        void run() throws Exception;\n    }\n}\n"}
